President Donald Trump has announced his plan to rebuild America's infrastructure, which is a critical aspect of his agenda to promote job creation and economic growth. Currently, America's infrastructure ranks 12th in the world, a situation that President Trump finds unacceptable. The President aims to reduce permitting time for infrastructure projects from 10 years to 2 years, and to streamline regulations to encourage growth and investment. He has allocated $200 billion in his budget for infrastructure, which can leverage a $1 trillion investment. The plan also includes investment in rural infrastructure and bold new transformative projects. Additionally, the President's plan emphasizes workforce training and skill-based apprenticeship education to prepare Americans for the future. Overall, President Trump's plan aims to make America's infrastructure the best in the world.